        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-3 mt-8">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-4 mb-8"><div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">How often do fire extinguishers need to be inspected in Greensboro, NC?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Monthly visual inspections by building staff, annual professional inspections by a licensed technician, 6-year internal examinations, and 12-year hydrostatic testing per NFPA 10 and the NC Fire Code (IFC-based).</p></div><div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">How much does a fire extinguisher inspection cost in Greensboro, NC?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Annual inspections in the Greensboro / Triad typically cost $14–$36 per unit. 6-year internal examinations run $24–$52. 12-year hydrostatic tests cost $30–$66. Volume discounts apply for 20+ units.</p></div><div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">Who can inspect fire extinguishers in Greensboro, NC?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Monthly visual checks by trained staff. Annual, 6-year, and 12-year service by a licensed technician. North Carolina requires fire extinguisher service contractors to hold licensing under NC law administered by the NC Office of State Fire Marshal (919-661-5880) through the NC Fire Protection Contractor Licensing Board. Verify your provider holds current NC credentials before scheduling service.</p></div><div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">What are the most common fire extinguisher violations in Greensboro?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600">The most common violations cited by the Greensboro Fire Department include: Missing Class K extinguishers in Downtown Greensboro and South Elm restaurant kitchens; Missing Class B coverage in Greensboro industrial and manufacturing facilities.</p></div><div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">Does Greensboro require fire extinguishers in all commercial buildings?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Yes. The NC Fire Code (IFC-based) requires portable fire extinguishers in all commercial, industrial, and multi-family residential buildings. Type, size, and placement depend on occupancy classification and hazard level per NFPA 10.</p></div></div>
